WEBVTT

00:00.254 --> 00:05.254
Subs by Raceman and Zhalom
www.forom.com

00:08.255 --> 00:10.578
<i>My name
is Melinda Gordon.</i>

00:10.873 --> 00:13.459
<i>I'm married,
I live in a small town,</i>

00:14.402 --> 00:16.116
<i>and I own
an antique shop.</i>

00:16.140 --> 00:18.105
<i>I might be just like you.</i>

00:18.135 --> 00:22.523
<i>Except that from the time I was a little
girl, I knew that I could talk to the dead.</i>

00:23.691 --> 00:26.681
<i>Earthbound spirits,
my grandmother called them.</i>

00:27.111 --> 00:29.583
<i>They're stuck here because they
have unfinished business with the living</i>

00:29.585 --> 00:31.891
<i>and they come to me
for help.</i>

00:34.728 --> 00:39.961
<i>In order to tell you my story,
I have to tell you theirs.</i>

00:42.122 --> 00:44.969
Are you serious?
Tonight?

00:45.917 --> 00:47.653
Yes, I've been dying
to see it.

00:48.536 --> 00:50.553
Are you kidding me,
I would love to.

00:50.596 --> 00:54.323
Oh, thank you so much.
I'll call you if the chest comes in.

00:54.358 --> 00:56.711
Yeah. We haven't
been to a movie in like 6 years.

00:56.748 --> 00:59.062
Oh, all right, maybe it's been
more like a month.

01:00.025 --> 01:02.343
No, it's a great idea.
It is.

01:02.526 --> 01:04.190
I'll close up early.

01:04.227 --> 01:07.430
You know, I'm sorry to cut you short,
but I have a little bit of a situation here.

01:07.475 --> 01:08.631
Yeah, I'll see you
at the house. Bye.

01:08.665 --> 01:11.331
Hey, do you really think
that I can't see what you're doing?

01:12.778 --> 01:15.031
First, no skates
in the store.

01:15.068 --> 01:17.251
They're heelys
not skates.

01:17.285 --> 01:21.532
All right, no wheels on your
feet allowed and, no shoplifting.

01:21.567 --> 01:22.671
I was gonna pay for it.

01:22.708 --> 01:24.010
You just didn't give me
the chance.

01:24.058 --> 01:26.040
They're $275 a piece.

01:26.087 --> 01:28.681
And the register is that way,
not out on the street.

01:28.716 --> 01:29.611
Whatever.

01:29.776 --> 01:31.932
- What's your phone number?
- Why?

01:31.967 --> 01:33.003
I'm calling your parents.

01:33.045 --> 01:35.101
- You gotta be kidding me.
- Nope.

01:36.547 --> 01:39.050
Look, my mother's sick.

01:39.427 --> 01:42.613
Real sick. And this
would really upset her.

01:43.015 --> 01:44.910
Do you really think
that I'm that out of it?

01:44.956 --> 01:47.511
Do you think that i am so un
hip that i would fall for that?

01:47.546 --> 01:48.412
Yeah.

01:48.447 --> 01:50.251
- What's your name?
- Ned.

01:50.296 --> 01:51.723
Ned, give me
your phone number,

01:51.757 --> 01:54.460
or I will take you and your
heelys down to the police station.

01:56.415 --> 01:58.303
I am so sorry.

01:58.335 --> 02:00.273
He has never done
anything like this before.

02:00.307 --> 02:01.042
No, it's fine.

02:01.077 --> 02:02.541
I just thought that you
would want to know.

02:02.586 --> 02:03.461
I was gonna
pay for them.

02:03.498 --> 02:07.942
Ned. It's not like he doesn't have
a ton of this stuff anyway.

02:08.164 --> 02:09.500
He's got
signed guitar picks,

02:09.536 --> 02:12.082
keith moon's drumsticks,
old ticket stubs.

02:12.316 --> 02:14.183
None of it stolen,
by the way.

02:15.406 --> 02:19.521
He will never come back in here
again, I can promise you that.

02:19.557 --> 02:21.272
I'm gonna go
wait outside.

02:21.315 --> 02:23.151
You don't have to
do that. He's welcome.

02:23.188 --> 02:25.731
Just with shoes
minus wheels.

02:26.897 --> 02:28.912
- You have kids?
- No.

02:29.827 --> 02:32.342
- No, not yet.
- Well, they're great.

02:33.028 --> 02:34.862
Until they become
teenagers.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.472
And then you realize
you're just being

02:36.515 --> 02:39.202
paid back double for all the rotten
things you did as a teenager.

02:39.237 --> 02:40.651
He seems like a good kid.

02:41.115 --> 02:42.721
He is. He is.

02:43.188 --> 02:45.340
It's just been a little
tough lately, you know?

02:45.615 --> 02:49.630
He's been so moody. He doesn't talk,
he hardly sleeps.

02:49.668 --> 02:53.050
'S just like his whole life
is this big secret all of a sudden.

02:54.178 --> 02:56.981
Anyway, you have
to get back to work, so do I.

02:58.426 --> 02:59.762
I'm Delia Banks
by the way.

02:59.797 --> 03:01.662
Oh, Melinda Gordon.
Nice to meet you.

03:01.708 --> 03:02.680
You look familiar.

03:02.717 --> 03:05.103
I run the real estate office
on the other side of the square.

03:05.147 --> 03:07.891
Oh, well, I'll see you
at village java.

03:07.928 --> 03:09.480
Every chance I get.

03:09.996 --> 03:12.150
Thank you.
And, uh...

03:12.188 --> 03:14.392
I guess I'll see you
around campus.

